Interface ManagedFilePath

All Known Implementing Classes:

public interface ManagedFilePath

Represents the path of a managed file.

getFileNameWithoutExtension

java.lang.String getFileNameWithoutExtension()
Returns the base name of this file. The base name is the last element of the file name. For example the base name of /somefolder/somefile is somefile. The root of a file system has an empty base name. Returns: The base name. Never returns null.

Returns:

getFileNameExtension

java.lang.String getFileNameExtension()
Returns the extension of this file name. Returns: The extension. Returns an empty string if the name has no extension.

Returns:

getNameCount

int getNameCount()
Returns the depth of this file name, within its file system. The depth of the root of a file system is 0. The depth of any other file is 1 + the depth of its parent.

Returns:

getName

java.lang.String getName(int index)

getPath

java.lang.String getPath()
Returns the absolute path of this file, within its file system. This path is normalised, so that . and .. elements have been removed. Also, the path only contains / as its separator character. The path always starts with / The root of a file system has / as its absolute path.

Returns:
The path. Never returns null.

resolve

ManagedFilePath resolve(ManagedFilePath path)
This method transforms the given name to a path using this path as basis. If this path represents /a/b then resolve will return /a/b/name. The path given must be relative.

Parameters:
